-- Everton Closes on $9 Million Bid for Jelavic, Express Says: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2012-01-30T10:26:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/everton-closes-on-9-million-bid-for-jelavic-express-says-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers with clickable links to the Web.  Everton Deal  Everton is close to signing Glasgow Rangers striker Nikica
Jelavic for about 6 million pounds ($9.4 million), the  Daily
Express  reported.  Jelavic told Rangers coach Ally McCoist he wants to move to
Goodison Park, the Express said.  Chelsea Bid  Chelsea bid 1 million pounds for Nottingham Forest’s
Patrick Bamford, who has played 12 minutes as a substitute for
his club’s first team, the  Daily Mail  reported.  The teenager has got nine goals in the last two academy
games for Forest, the Mail said.  QPR Deals  Queens Park Rangers are seeking to sign former Liverpool
striker Djibril Cisse on loan from Lazio, the  Daily Mail 
reported.  QPR are also close to hiring Nancy midfielder Samba
Diakite, who is part of Mali’s African Nations Cup squad,
according to the Mail.  Sunderland Recruit  Bolton may trade striker  Kevin Davies  to Sunderland for
about 500,000 pounds, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  The Black Cats need cover as loan signing Nicklas Bendtner
is out of action with a broken nose, the Mirror said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
